&quot;Yale, the reactor-reprocessing-bomb route is only one of the many ways of acquiring a WMD. It is by no means the best one if you are trying to build a clandestine one. Proliferation is, to my mind, more of a social and political problem, rather than merely a technical one &quot;<br>
<br>
The key word in your post is &quot;merely&quot; - which I read as &quot;solely&quot;.<br>
True of course. One needs the volition to aquire. However, almost all methods of aquisition are based on extremely specific dual use technologies. As experts have pointed out, the international acceptance of the absolute truth of the proposition that ANY and ALL nuclear technologies are INHERENTLY of military potential would lead to a virtual evaporation of proliferation. ALL nuclear weapon paths REQUIRE the acquistion of actinides, and the technologies to extract, manipulate and detonate them.<br>
<br>
By recognizing the alloyed truth, the &quot;civillian&quot; cover for LATENT proliferation - the method used by ALL weapons states after the US and USSR would disapear. The production, extraction, and manipulation of actinides, <br>
the technologies for the production, extraction, and manipulation of actinides,<br>
 the training required for the production, extraction, and manipulation of actinides, <br>
the financing for the production, extraction, and manipulation of actinides,<br>
 the innocent &quot;cover&quot; for the production, extraction, and manipulation of actinides, etc <br>
would suddenly be unambigously MILITARY in nature, leading to a sea-change in availability.<br>
<br>
You pointed out the Devil's Bargain yourself:<br>
&quot;Concievably one may be able to use this system to induce fission in U238 providing a safe, non-critical source of Atomic energy that does not require the production of Plutonium &quot;<br>
<br>
And what does fissioning U238 - ALWAYS, as a law of nature - produce? Streams of neutrons! And what does this flux of neutrons in the presence of the U238 produce? Plutonium 239. This cannot be avoided. Any nation using this system will simply have a bomb-making factory.<br>
<br>
You CANNOT use ANY technology that uses or creates actinides without creating the potential for bomb-making. Without them you DON'T have the potential for nuclear bomb-making.<br>
<br>
It is a pretty binary choice.<br>
<br>
This was recognized at the very beginning of the Nuclear Age, but Eisenhower, in a bonehead policy of Earth-shattering stupidity, ignored the official recommendations, and created the &quot;Atoms For Peace&quot; program - a complete disaster.<br>
<br>
<br>
